definitions.definition: A branching-out , the act or result of developing branches ; specifically the divergence of the stem and limbs of a plant into smaller ones, or of similar developments in blood vessels , anatomical structures etc.
An offshoot of a decision, fact etc.; a consequence or implication , especially one which complicates a situation.

main_definition: ( botany , anatomy , also figurative ) A branching-out , the act or result of developing branches ; specifically the divergence of the stem and limbs of a plant into smaller ones, or of similar developments in blood vessels , anatomical structures etc.
secondary_definitions: ( figurative , often in the plural ) An offshoot of a decision, fact etc.; a consequence or implication , especially one which complicates a situation.
